yder
------------------------------------------
Simple and easy to use logging library. You can log messages to the console, a
file, syslog or journald.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.11.2-1
  liborcania-devel-1.2.9-1bl1
  liborcania1.2-1.2.9-1bl1
  libyder-devel-1.4.4-1bl1
  libyder1.4-1.4.4-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2
  ninja-1.8.2-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/babelouest/yder

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/babelouest/yder/archive/v1.4.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack yder-1.4.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./yder-1.4.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/yder-1.4.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/yder-1.4.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libyder1.4-1.4.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libyder-devel-1.4.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(yder)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/yder.README
  /usr/share/doc/yder/ChangeLog.md
  /usr/share/doc/yder/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/yder/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/yder/examples/Makefile
  /usr/share/doc/yder/examples/log_callback.c
  /usr/share/doc/yder/examples/log_combined.c
  /usr/share/doc/yder/examples/log_console.c
  /usr/share/doc/yder/examples/log_file.c
  /usr/share/doc/yder/examples/log_journald.c
  /usr/share/doc/yder/examples/log_syslog.c

(libyder1.4)
  /usr/bin/cygyder-1.4.dll

(libyder-devel)
  /usr/include/yder-cfg.h
  /usr/include/yder.h
  /usr/lib/libyder.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libyder.pc

